{
  "texts": [
    "This confusion may partially account for the low sentiment score for AEB, where false-positive braking interventions are typically ascribed to AEB, rather than ACC.",
    "Furthermore, for AEB, it is predominantly these false positives that drivers perceive, while the number of instances in which AEB averts accidents is logically low (78), since (near-)accidents are infrequent events.",
    "However, from a cost-benefit perspective, the AEB system might still be beneficial despite the low sentiment score, considering the substantial costs of accidents.",
    "The acceptance of technology by drivers is essential, particularly in the context of the increasing mandating of technological systems in trucks.",
    "As of November 2015, EU regulations have made it compulsory for all new trucks to be equipped with AEB and LDW systems (79)."
  ]
}